'''Smoking in Macau''' is regulated more strictly than in [[mainland China]], but not to the extent of the regulation of [[smoking in Hong Kong]].
In May 2009 the government of [[Macau Special Administrative Region]] (SAR) announced a planned indoor [[smoking ban]] for all public places,<ref name="Macao to ban 11464428">{{cite news | url= http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2009-05/31/content_11464428.htm | title= Macao to ban indoor smoking in public places | publisher= [[Xinhua]] | date= 2009-05-31 }}</ref> "to create a fair environment where smokers have the freedom to smoke and non-smokers also have the freedom not to inhale [[second-hand smoke]]," Health Bureau director Lei Chin Ion said.<ref name="UO Macau">{{cite web | url= http://www.uomacau.com/en-us/entertainment/detail/2336?position_id=33&thread=1735 | title= Gov't to ban smoking in indoor public places | publisher= UO Macau }}</ref> In April 2009 the government of Macau SAR announced proposed legislation that sought to raise the tobacco [[sales tax]] by 300%.<ref name="Zheng Limin cctv">{{cite news | last= Zheng | first= Limin | url= http://www.cctv.com/program/bizchina/20090501/101236.shtml | title= Macao to raise tobacco tax by 300% | publisher= [[Xinhua]] | date= 2009-01-05 }}</ref> Smoking is not banned in Macau's [[casino]]s,<ref name="eyeonasia 2009 05">{{cite web | url= http://www.businessweek.com/globalbiz/blog/eyeonasia/archives/2009/05/at_first_glance.html | title= Macau Should Ban Smoking in Casinos | publisher= Bloomberg [[Businessweek]] | date= May 3, 2009 }}</ref> which are a major aspect of [[tourism in Macau]]. A majority of Macau residents support a total ban on smoking in public places,<ref name="back smoking ban">{{cite news | url= http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2006-03/22/content_549402.htm | title= Survey: 72% back smoking ban in Macao | publisher= [[Xinhua]] | date= 2006-03-22 }}</ref> but lawmakers in [[closed session]] on 20 April 2010 were unable to reach a consensus regarding a total ban inside casinos.<ref name="Natalie Divergent opinions">{{cite news | last= Leung | first= Natalie | url= http://www.macaudailytimes.com.mo/macau/11370-Divergent-opinions-smoking-ban.html | title= Divergent opinions on smoking ban | publisher= | date= 2010-04-21 }}</ref> The increasing number of smokers is a cause for concern,<ref name="back smoking ban" /> as 17% of people in Macau smoke.<ref name="cctv 20090601">{{cite news | last= Zhang | first= Ning | url= http://english.cctv.com/20090601/100977.shtml | title= Macao to ban indoor smoking in public places | publisher= [[Xinhua]] | date= 2009-06-01 }}</ref>
==See also== * [[Healthcare in Macau]]
